author: wsjcom
title: Ex-TD Bank Executive Pleads Guilty to Role in Ponzi Scheme
text:
MIAMI—A former executive at Toronto-Dominion Bank pleaded guilty Thursday to a federal conspiracy charge for providing false assurances to investors who put their money in ex-lawyer Scott Rothstein’s $1.2 billion Ponzi scheme.
Frank Spinosa, a former bank regional vice president, pleaded guilty in Miami federal court to wire fraud conspiracy after reaching a plea deal with prosecutors. Mr. Spinosa, 54, faces a maximum of five years in...
